Michael Jordan was born in 1963 in Brooklyn. He played in the NBA from 1984 to 2003, primarily for the Chicago Bulls. Known by his nickname "Air Jordan", he is considered one of the greatest basketball players of all time. In the 1980s, Jordan led the Chicago Bulls to numerous titles and became a global sports icon known for his athleticism and skill on the court. Off the court, he became one of the most marketed athletes through endorsement deals with major brands like Nike, Coca-Cola, and McDonald's.
